{{Infobox video game |image=3-2-1, Rattle Battle! Coverart.png |caption = |developer = [[Tecmo]] |publisher = [[Koei Tecmo|Tecmo Koei Games]] |designer = |released = {{vgrelease|JP|March 31, 2009<ref name="JP release">{{cite web| script-title=ja:あつい12ゲーム フリフリパーティー！ | url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/wii/wiiware/wcuj/index.html | publisher=[[Nintendo]] | language=Japanese | accessdate=2011-08-13}}</ref>|PAL|August 14, 2009<ref name="PAL release">{{cite news|title=Discover this week's range of new software to download via the Wii Shop Channel and Nintendo DSi Shop|url=https://www.nintendo.co.uk/NOE/en_GB/news/2009/discover_this_weeks_range_of_new_software_to_download_via_the_wii_shop_channel_and_nintendo_dsi_shop_14370.html|publisher=Nintendo of Europe|date=2009-08-14|accessdate=2009-09-02}}</ref>|NA|August 31, 2009<ref name="NA release">{{cite news|title=Pirates, Puzzles, Rattlers and Role-Playing|url=https://www.nintendo.com/whatsnew/detail/jw6qAPPxrcP8t2FwKYU9l2gWpq2sVJ3P|publisher=Nintendo of America|date=2009-08-31|accessdate=2009-09-02}}</ref>}} |genre = [[Action game|Action]] ([[Minigame|minigame compilation]]) |modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]] |platforms = [[WiiWare]] }}
'''''3-2-1, Rattle Battle!''''', known in Japan as {{nihongo|'''''Atsui 12 Game: Furi Furi Party!'''''|あつい12ゲーム フリフリパーティー！}}, is a [[video game]] for [[WiiWare]] developed by [[Tecmo]]. It was released in Japan on March 31, 2009, the PAL regions on August 14, 2009<ref name="PAL release"/> and in North America on August 31, 2009.<ref name="NA release"/>
==Gameplay== ''3-2-1, Rattle Battle!'' is a collection of twelve [[minigame]]s that generally revolve around players shaking the [[Wii Remote]] in order to score points. Controlling a blue cartoon mascot named "Rattle Hero", shaking the Wii Remote causes him to perform a different action depending on the minigame. These include firing a laser beam to dispatch enemies, bouncing up and down to weigh down a scale and growing or shrinking in size to dodge a salvo of arrows.<ref name=sili>[http://www.siliconera.com/2009/03/31/this-tecmo-wiiware-game-is-just-about-shaking/ This Tecmo WiiWare Game Is Just About Shaking]</ref> Each minigame lasts between just three seconds to around two minutes in length.
The game features online leaderboards for high scores for two of the minigames.<ref name=sili/>
==Development== A prototype for ''3-2-1, Rattle Battle!'', then titled ''Playshake'', was demonstrated at the 2009 [[Tokyo Game Show]]. The prototype featured minimal graphics and only a single minigame in which the player had to shake the Wii Remote as many times as they can in three seconds.<ref>[http://www.joystiq.com/2008/10/30/playshake-the-game-you-play-by-shaking/ Playshake: the game you play by shaking]</ref>
