'''BĪŽAN-NAMA''' ({{lang-fa|بیژن نامه}}) is a [[Persian literature|Persian]] epic poem of ca. 1,900 couplets relating the adventures of the legendary hero [[Bijan and Manijeh|Bīžan]] son of [[Shahnameh|Giv]].<ref>William Hanaway, Jr., "BĪŽAN-NAMA" in Encyclopaedia Iranica. [http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/bizan-nama-an-epic-poem-of-ca] accessed February 2011</ref> Zabiollah Safa, an Iranian literary scholars notes that a large number verses of thies epic were taken from the Bīžan and Manīža in Ferdowsī’s Šāh-nāma. [[Jalal Matini]] after closely postulated that the epic is mainly a copy of Ferdowsī’s story with some verses added by the author and some of [[Ferdowsi]]’s omitted.
